list.name: Changes
list.comment:
Refactor benchmark test for RowsToJson.
Move query execution inside loop and add error handling for RowsToJson conversion. This ensures each iteration starts with a fresh query and catches potential errors during the conversion process.

MESSAGE.value:
Remove IntelliJ project configuration files
This commit deletes several .idea directory files, including .gitignore, dataSources.xml, modules.xml, sql2json.iml, inspectionProfiles/Project_Default.xml, sqldialects.xml, and vcs.xml. These changes clean up project-specific settings and metadata, ensuring that local development environments remain consistent and isolated.

Add IntelliJ IDEA project structure files
This commit includes configuration files essential for setting up the IntelliJ IDEA project. It adds data source configuration, module settings, VCS mappings, and workspace properties, ensuring the project is correctly set up for MariaDB and Git integration.

Add new data source configuration for MariaDB
This commit introduces a new XML configuration file for the MariaDB data source in the project. The configuration includes extensive details on database grants, server version, and supported collations, improving the database management capabilities.

Add corrupted data source files for diagnostics
Included .reason.txt and .xml files to log issues with a corrupted data source in the .idea folder. These additions provide essential error logs and database model information to aid in debugging persistence problems within the database storage backend.

Add profiling output files for CPU and memory
Add CPU and memory profiling output files to the repository, which will assist in performance analysis and optimization. These files can be used to identify bottlenecks and improve the application's efficiency.

Add inspection profile for Go error handling
Created a new inspection profile named "Project Default" in the .idea directory. This profile enables error handling warnings for specific methods across various Go packages, ensuring unhandled error results are flagged.

Add corrupted data source files for diagnostics
Included .reason.txt and .xml files to log issues related to a corrupted data source in the .idea folder. These files provide necessary error logs and database model information to aid in troubleshooting persistence issues within the database storage backend.

Refactor benchmark test for RowsToJson.
Move query execution inside loop and add error handling for RowsToJson conversion. This ensures each iteration starts with a fresh query and catches potential errors during the conversion process.
